title: Narrative

* This example shows the `template` parameter of the tabbed toc macros

* The selected tiddler is shown in the content pane using the [[myTemplate]] tiddler as a [[template|TemplateTiddlers]]

* The state tiddler is preset to [[aa]], so the template rendering is visible right away

{{example-overview}}

+
title: Description

TOC Macro Parameter "template"
+
title: myTemplate

<h2>Template: <$view field="title"/></h2>

<$transclude $mode="block"/>
+
title: $:/temp/toc/demoSelected

aa
+
title: Output

The `template` parameter defines how the selected tiddler is shown in the content pane.

<$macrocall
	$name="toc-tabbed-internal-nav"
	tag="Contents"
	selectedTiddler="$:/temp/toc/demoSelected"
	unselectedText="<p>Select a topic in the table of contents.</p>"
	missingText="<p>Missing tiddler.</p>"
	template="myTemplate"
/>
